# Implementation checklist (115.md)

Use this checklist when implementing or reviewing the Interview Practice app. Tick items as done.

**Focus:** Technical interview prep (coding questions, system design, algorithms, etc.).

## Setup

- [x] Node on LTS (if needed)
- [x] pnpm installed; use it for the project (lighter and faster than npm). Create app with `pnpm create next-app@latest`
- [x] Next.js app created
- [x] OpenAI API key obtained and stored securely (env var, not in code)

## Core app

- [x] **Single page** with:
  - [x] User input (e.g. topic, difficulty, or type: coding / system design / algorithms)
  - [x] Button to request prep
  - [x] Area to show AI response
- [x] **API route** (e.g. `app/api/prep/route.ts`):
  - [x] Receives user input
  - [x] Calls the OpenAI API with chosen model
  - [x] Uses a system prompt (technical interviewer)
- [x] One of the allowed models in use: GPT-4.1, GPT-4.1 mini, GPT-4.1 nano, GPT-4o, GPT-4o mini
- [x] System prompt defines the model as a technical interviewer (coding, system design, algorithms)

## Task requirements (115.md)

- [x] **At least 5 system prompts** with different techniques (e.g. few-shot, Chain-of-Thought, zero-shot); compare and use what works best
- [x] **At least one OpenAI setting** tuned (e.g. temperature, top_p, frequency_penalty)
- [x] **At least one security guard** (e.g. input validation, prompt validation, rate limiting) to prevent misuse

## Optional (see 115.md)

- [x] Temperature slider (user can tune in UI)
- [x] Job description field (paste job posting for tailored practice)
- [x] deployed on [Vercel](https://ai-powered-interview-app-nu.vercel.app/)
